who was the producer of Batman and also produced The Green Hornet.

800
00:46:46,730 --> 00:46:51,690
字幕
The murders were then followed up the very next night by more murders.

801
00:46:51,690 --> 00:46:57,070
字幕
It was just a nightmare and very scary for Bruce, too,

802
00:46:57,070 --> 00:47:01,920
字幕
because Bruce's whole mentality was protection, to take care of us.

803
00:47:02,100 --> 00:47:03,730
字幕
One officer summed up the murders:

804
00:47:03,730 --> 00:47:09,130
字幕
"In all my years I have never seen anything like this before."

805
00:47:14,140 --> 00:47:17,230
字幕
Those were tough times, going out of the '60s and into the '70s.

806
00:47:17,230 --> 00:47:21,290
字幕
And every day, I practise martial arts.

807
00:47:21,290 --> 00:47:24,240
字幕
We were really struggling financially to make it,

808
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:29,110
字幕
and we had bought our first house which we ended up not being able to afford.

809
00:47:29,110 --> 00:47:31,270
字幕
And right in the middle of that he hurt his back.

810
00:47:31,270 --> 00:47:34,930
字幕
He was doing a good morning stretch exercise which can be very dangerous.

811
00:47:34,930 --> 00:47:36,910
字幕
Chiropractors like that exercise.

812
00:47:36,910 --> 00:47:38,220
字幕
- You see? - Watch out.

813
00:47:38,220 --> 00:47:41,810
字幕
For whatever reason, he did not warm up and just... that was it.

814
00:47:41,810 --> 00:47:43,680
字幕
He was in excruciating pain.

815
00:47:43,680 --> 00:47:47,360
字幕
I said, "Where's Bruce?" They never wanted to say he hurt his back,

816
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:50,120
字幕
because I knew he was working on the screen scripts.

817
00:47:50,120 --> 00:47:53,770
字幕
They told him that he was never going to walk properly,

818
00:47:53,770 --> 00:47:56,200
字幕
and forget doing any gung fu.

819
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:59,860
字幕
On the back of his business card he wrote the words "Walk on".

820
00:47:59,970 --> 00:48:05,080
字幕
He used to put the card on his bathroom mirror and his doors and walls,

821
00:48:05,080 --> 00:48:08,200
字幕
so everywhere he went in his room, he'd see "Walk on".

822
00:48:08,200 --> 00:48:10,580
字幕
So he'd get down and start doing his stretching.

823
00:48:10,580 --> 00:48:14,420
字幕
Bruce brought himself back through rigorous rehabilitation.

824
00:48:14,420 --> 00:48:16,110
字幕
I had a similar expression

825
00:48:16,110 --> 00:48:19,770
字幕
when I would drive down to Torrance to do my jiujitsu class every week.

826
00:48:19,770 --> 00:48:23,900
字幕
His expression was "Walk on" and mine was "Walk in the front door".

827
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:26,650
字幕
I had every excuse on the way down to go back.

828
00:48:26,650 --> 00:48:29,720
字幕
My stomach hurts. My arm hurts. My knee's aching.

829
00:48:29,720 --> 00:48:33,500
字幕
And I used to say, "Walk in the front door. Walk in the front door."

830
00:48:33,730 --> 00:48:37,980
字幕
The end result of walking in that front door 16 years was I got my black belt,

831
00:48:37,980 --> 00:48:40,490
字幕
which I consider the greatest achievement of my life,

832
00:48:41,330 --> 00:48:42,680
字幕
apart from my children.

833
00:48:43,070 --> 00:48:46,560
字幕
The back problem was a constant problem in his filming

834
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:48,340
字幕
from day one after the injury.

835
00:48:48,340 --> 00:48:50,340
字幕
Something he had to be careful about

836
00:48:50,340 --> 00:48:54,360
字幕
and nurse each day when he finished working.

837
00:48:54,770 --> 00:48:59,020
字幕
And you push it out, but all the time you are keeping the continuity going.

838
00:48:59,020 --> 00:49:01,930
字幕
Bending, stretching.

839
00:49:01,930 --> 00:49:04,400
字幕
He worked extremely hard.

840
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:07,890
字幕
Most of us, I think, don't know what it is to work that hard.

841
00:49:11,230 --> 00:49:13,400
字幕
My father went to India

842
00:49:13,400 --> 00:49:16,410
字幕
with James Coburn and the writer Stirling Silliphant.

843
00:49:16,410 --> 00:49:19,760
字幕
They were scouting locations for a film, The Silent Flute,

844
00:49:19,760 --> 00:49:21,970
字幕
that my father had written the treatment for

845
00:49:21,970 --> 00:49:24,690
字幕
that he was really hoping would come together,

846
00:49:24,690 --> 00:49:28,590
字幕
because he was struggling at that point in time to get a project going.

847
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:32,550
字幕
The Silent Flute could have blasted Bruce into Hollywood big time.

848
00:49:32,550 --> 00:49:35,870
字幕
This was going to be the big breakthrough project.

849
00:49:35,870 --> 00:49:39,350
字幕
This was going to put money in the bank to pay the mortgage and all that.

850
00:49:39,350 --> 00:49:42,530
字幕
But they couldn't find the locations that they wanted.

851
00:49:42,530 --> 00:49:45,940
字幕
Stirling and Jim came back to Warner Bros

852
00:49:45,940 --> 00:49:49,910
字幕
and said, "This is just not what we're looking for in location."

853
00:49:49,910 --> 00:49:52,190
字幕
And then it all came crashing down.

854
00:49:55,150 --> 00:49:57,510
字幕
That was such a disappointment to Bruce

855
00:49:57,510 --> 00:50:00,740
字幕
because we were banking on it, literally.

856
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:21,020
字幕
Bruce took a trip back to Hong Kong to help his mom

857
00:50:21,020 --> 00:50:23,150
字幕
with immigration into the United States.

858
00:50:23,150 --> 00:50:26,150
字幕
He took Brandon took with him. Brandon was five years old.

859
00:50:26,150 --> 00:50:29,520
字幕
He wasn't working, had no money. He dropped everything.

860
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:31,640
字幕
Closed his schools. "I'm going to Hong Kong."

861
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:35,940
字幕
The Green Hornet was at that time showing on TV in Hong Kong,

862
00:50:35,940 --> 00:50:38,180
字幕
only the people were calling it The Kato Show.

863
00:50:38,180 --> 00:50:41,060
字幕
They didn't care about Van Williams. He was the biggest thing there.

864
00:50:41,060 --> 00:50:44,830
字幕
He was greeted there as a returning star.

865
00:50:44,830 --> 00:50:48,850
字幕
That was the first time he thought, "Wow. People recognise me here."

866
00:50:48,850 --> 00:50:50,050
字幕
"They remember me."

867
00:50:50,050 --> 00:50:52,780
字幕
He did a couple of interviews on television shows.

868
00:50:52,780 --> 00:50:56,080
字幕
Oh, yeah, that kid. Now he's a big star in Hollywood.

869
00:50:57,820 --> 00:50:59,440
字幕
So that was the first inkling

870
00:50:59,440 --> 00:51:02,720
字幕
that maybe there would be a future there in Hong Kong.

871
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:05,220
字幕
But he wasn't quite ready to follow up on that.

872
00:51:08,310 --> 00:51:12,340
字幕
Bruce Lee had a bit part, or a supporting role,

873
00:51:12,340 --> 00:51:14,480
字幕
in the Longstreet series.

874
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:17,800
字幕
And this had an enormous effect on the audience. What was it?

875
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:21,320
字幕
I think the successful ingredient in it

876
00:51:21,320 --> 00:51:25,040
字幕
was because I was being Bruce Lee.

877
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:26,850
字幕
- Yourself? - Myself, right.

878
00:51:26,850 --> 00:51:30,340
字幕
And did that part, just expressed myself, like I say,

879
00:51:30,340 --> 00:51:32,510
字幕
honestly expressed myself at that time.

880
00:51:32,510 --> 00:51:35,920
字幕
He was very proud of Longstreet, and it was very much from him

881
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:37,790
字幕
and his art and his thoughts.

882
00:51:37,790 --> 00:51:41,330
字幕
Can you remember the lines by Stirling Silliphant to...

883
00:51:41,330 --> 00:51:43,250
字幕
- He's one of my students. - Was he, too?

884
00:51:43,250 --> 00:51:46,300
字幕
- Yes. - You've had everybody as your student.

885
00:51:46,740 --> 00:51:49,090
字幕
But some lines there expressed your philosophy.

886
00:51:49,090 --> 00:51:51,360
字幕
- I don't know if you remember them. - I remember.

887
00:51:51,360 --> 00:51:54,090
字幕
I said... This is what it is, OK?

888
00:51:54,090 --> 00:51:57,200
字幕
If you try to remember, you will lose.

889
00:51:57,200 --> 00:51:59,060
字幕
I said empty your mind.

890
00:51:59,790 --> 00:52:02,570
字幕
Be formless, shapeless.

891
00:52:02,750 --> 00:52:03,890
字幕
Like water.

892
00:52:04,930 --> 00:52:06,860
字幕
Now, you put water into a cup,

893
00:52:07,180 --> 00:52:08,870
字幕
it becomes the cup.

894
00:52:08,870 --> 00:52:11,170
字幕
Put water into a bottle, it becomes the bottle.

895
00:52:11,170 --> 00:52:14,290
字幕
You put it in a teapot, it becomes the teapot.

896
00:52:14,380 --> 00:52:19,330
字幕
Now, water can flow or creep or drip or crash.

897
00:52:19,860 --> 00:52:21,600
字幕
Be water, my friend.

898
00:52:21,600 --> 00:52:23,840
字幕
- Like that. You see? - I see. I get the idea.

899
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:26,270
字幕
- A-ha. - I get the power behind it.

900
00:52:26,270 --> 00:52:29,080
字幕
The thing that I got off him the most is the trust,

901
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:33,320
字幕
being able to trust your abilities in each situation.

902
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:36,340
字幕
A lot of times the game becomes too scripted.

903
00:52:36,340 --> 00:52:37,920
字幕
When it's too scripted

904
00:52:37,920 --> 00:52:40,700
字幕
and you start planning for certain things to take place,

905
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:43,660
字幕
that's when I believe you're weak.

906
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:46,030
字幕
What he's saying is that you have to adapt

907
00:52:46,030 --> 00:52:48,000
字幕
to your surroundings, your environment.

908
00:52:48,000 --> 00:52:51,030
字幕
James Coburn said, "Look, man, the best thing you can do,

909
00:52:51,030 --> 00:52:55,500
字幕
go back to Hong Kong, do what you do best, come back, rock the world."

910
00:52:55,500 --> 00:53:00,840
字幕
James Coburn did tell Bruce that he shouldn't keep doing TV,

911
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:03,060
字幕
that it would eat up his genius.

912
00:53:03,060 --> 00:53:07,910
字幕
He had much more to offer the world and he should hold out for starring roles.

913
00:53:07,910 --> 00:53:11,760
字幕
Jimi Hendrix had to break away and go to England to be recognised

914
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:13,730
字幕
as the rock star that he was.

915
00:53:13,730 --> 00:53:16,130
字幕
Clint Eastwood, he had a career out of Rawhide,

916
00:53:16,130 --> 00:53:19,360
字幕
but it was the Italian Westerns that really made his career.

917
00:53:19,360 --> 00:53:21,960
字幕
Bruce ultimately had to go back to Hong Kong

918
00:53:21,960 --> 00:53:24,560
字幕
to be recognised as the movie star he was.

919
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:28,490
字幕
Here's a plane ticket. Just go back to Hong Kong for a few years.

920
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:31,550
字幕
You wouldn't want any trouble, huh?

921
00:53:31,550 --> 00:53:33,490
字幕
That's one of the things I admire most about him.

922
00:53:33,490 --> 00:53:36,660
字幕
He said, "OK, the institution's not gonna work for me."

923
00:53:36,660 --> 00:53:38,240
字幕
"I'll figure something else out."

924
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:39,810
字幕
He just went to through back door.

925
00:53:50,070 --> 00:53:54,910
字幕
Bruce made the first two pictures with independent producer Raymond Chow

926
00:53:54,910 --> 00:53:56,910
字幕
for $15,000 each.

927
00:53:56,910 --> 00:54:01,570
字幕
That was... It was made in Thailand in a small village in Thailand.

928
00:54:01,740 --> 00:54:04,500
字幕
Bruce Lee plays a working-class hero.

929
00:54:04,500 --> 00:54:06,930
字幕
He's from the land. He's one of the folk.

930
00:54:06,930 --> 00:54:09,530
字幕
But at the same time as that, he's never one of the guys.

931
00:54:10,160 --> 00:54:13,770
字幕
And this is why it was so successful, as well as the brilliant choreography.

932
00:54:16,330 --> 00:54:20,050
字幕
Bruce Lee completely changed the way action scenes look today in cinema.

933
00:54:20,050 --> 00:54:22,720
字幕
It's about making violence look beautiful,

934
00:54:22,720 --> 00:54:24,660
字幕
which may sound like a paradox, it probably is,

935
00:54:24,660 --> 00:54:28,710
字幕
but a director like John Woo, he shoots a gunfight like martial arts.

936
00:54:28,710 --> 00:54:34,420
字幕
It's a ballet. In terms of the craft of filmmaking, that's a huge change.

937
00:54:34,420 --> 00:54:38,980
字幕
But the Western movies really piss me off. They chop 'em up so much.

938
00:54:38,980 --> 00:54:42,200
字幕
Most of the scenes overzoom, so you can't see what's going on.

939
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:44,890
字幕
Those guys have to go back and watch Bruce Lee movies.

940
00:54:44,890 --> 00:54:48,430
字幕
You can see these awesome moves he's doing in their entirety.

941
00:54:48,430 --> 00:54:51,930
字幕
You can have a shot that doesn't have to last only a half-second long.

942
00:54:51,930 --> 00:54:54,760
字幕
I never even thought about it until I did this movie Haywire.

943
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:57,780
字幕
Now every time I see a movie, I'm like, "Stop cutting away."

944
00:54:57,780 --> 00:54:59,290
字幕
"Oh, that's a stunt double."

945
00:54:59,370 --> 00:55:03,860
字幕
They were wonderful to watch. No wires, no gimmicks, no quick cuts.

946
00:55:03,860 --> 00:55:07,630
字幕
You get an actor to portray that, you're gonna have to do quick cuts.

947
00:55:07,630 --> 00:55:09,220
字幕
Bruce Lee set a new baseline.

948
00:55:09,220 --> 00:55:13,650
字幕
Every piece of film fight choreography has been influenced by Bruce Lee,

949
00:55:13,650 --> 00:55:15,450
字幕
whether the people involved know it or not.

950
00:55:15,450 --> 00:55:18,120
字幕
- A motion picture is motion. - Yeah.

951
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:21,550
字幕
I mean, you gotta keep the dialogue down.

952
00:55:23,700 --> 00:55:26,140
字幕
We came over to Hong Kong

953
00:55:26,140 --> 00:55:29,470
字幕
and that was when they showed the premiere of The Big Boss.

954
00:55:30,640 --> 00:55:32,680
字幕
The theatre was packed.

955
00:55:33,110 --> 00:55:35,700
字幕
Bruce and I sat there towards the back.

956
00:55:36,540 --> 00:55:39,890
字幕
When Bruce Lee's first movie showed in Hollywood,

957
00:55:39,890 --> 00:55:42,170
字幕
I was so elated, I was so emotional,

958
00:55:42,170 --> 00:55:44,810
字幕
seeing my friend, my teacher, on the screen.

959
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:52,030
字幕
When the movie finishes, it is so quiet...

960
00:55:54,570 --> 00:55:56,410
字幕
you could hear a pin drop.

961
00:55:56,410 --> 00:55:59,420
字幕
And Bruce is like, "Oh, no. They hate it." You know.

962
00:55:59,420 --> 00:56:01,220
字幕
And all of a sudden...

963
00:56:02,980 --> 00:56:05,390
字幕
a huge roar goes up.

964
00:56:05,390 --> 00:56:10,710
字幕
And they're cheering and laughing and clapping. It was wonderful.

965
00:56:10,710 --> 00:56:14,570
字幕
Every time he came on and did his fight scene, everybody applauded.

966
00:56:14,570 --> 00:56:18,390
字幕
That's when we knew he was a movie star now.

967
00:56:18,490 --> 00:56:21,640
字幕
And then they started to spot Bruce in the audience.

968
00:56:26,460 --> 00:56:29,040
字幕
They carried him out on their shoulders.

969
00:56:29,040 --> 00:56:32,820
字幕
Oh, it was thrilling. It was thrilling to him.

970
00:56:32,820 --> 00:56:36,310
字幕
"Finally I have been appreciated in my work."

971
00:56:36,750 --> 00:56:40,730
字幕
It was wonderful, a very high moment in his life.

972
00:56:42,290 --> 00:56:44,260
字幕
It's The Pierre Berton Show,

973
00:56:44,260 --> 00:56:47,800
字幕
the programme that comes to you from the major capitals of the world.

974
00:56:47,800 --> 00:56:50,670
字幕
This edition comes to you from Hong Kong.

975
00:56:50,950 --> 00:56:54,480
字幕
And Pierre's guest, the newest Mandarin superstar.

976
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:58,650
字幕
His name is Bruce Lee and he doesn't even speak Mandarin.

977
00:56:58,790 --> 00:56:59,970
字幕
Here's Pierre.

978
00:57:01,180 --> 00:57:02,180
字幕
There's a pretty good chance

979
00:57:02,180 --> 00:57:05,220
字幕
that you'll get a TV series in the States called The Warrior

980
00:57:05,220 --> 00:57:09,220
字幕
in which you use, what, the martial arts in a Western setting?

981
00:57:09,550 --> 00:57:11,410
字幕
That was the original idea.

982
00:57:11,410 --> 00:57:14,030
字幕
Bruce Lee had an idea for a TV show called The Warrior,

983
00:57:14,030 --> 00:57:17,550
字幕
which later became the series Kung Fu, which we all know and love.

984
00:57:17,550 --> 00:57:19,240
字幕
David Carradine did a good job,

985
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:22,490
字幕
but Kung Fu, the TV series, was Bruce Lee's role.

986
00:57:22,490 --> 00:57:25,400
字幕
The better guy doesn't always get the job in the movie business.

987
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:27,690
字幕
There's a lot of politics involved.

988
00:57:27,690 --> 00:57:29,870
字幕
Have people come up in the industry and said,

989
00:57:29,870 --> 00:57:32,670
字幕
"We don't know how the audience are going to take a non-American?"

990
00:57:35,290 --> 00:57:38,440
字幕
Well, such question has been raised.

991
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:40,770
字幕
In fact, it is being discussed,

992
00:57:40,770 --> 00:57:44,320
字幕
and that is why The Warrior probably is not gonna be on.

993
00:57:44,320 --> 00:57:45,480
字幕
- I see. - You see?

994
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:51,870
字幕
Because unfortunately such thing does exist in this world.

995
00:57:51,870 --> 00:57:55,310
字幕
Bruce Lee was a bigger star, both in Asia and America.

996
00:57:55,310 --> 00:57:58,110
字幕
He was a world-class martial artist.

997
00:57:58,110 --> 00:57:59,970
字幕
He had already done The Green Hornet.

998
00:57:59,970 --> 00:58:03,080
字幕
And then he did not get the role for being too Asian.

999
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:06,650
字幕
He had such disdain for Hollywood

1000
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,490
字幕
and all those old movies

1001
00:58:08,490 --> 00:58:13,660
字幕
having Caucasian people play the parts of Chinese characters.

1002
00:58:17,650 --> 00:58:20,020
字幕
I have already made up my mind

1003
00:58:20,390 --> 00:58:24,210
字幕
that in the United States I think something about the Oriental,

1004
00:58:24,210 --> 00:58:28,850
字幕
I mean, the true Oriental, should be shown.

1005
00:58:28,850 --> 00:58:31,940
字幕
- Hollywood sure as heck hasn't. - You better believe it, man.

1006
00:58:31,940 --> 00:58:34,860
字幕
It's always the pigtail and bouncing around, chop-chop,

1007
00:58:34,860 --> 00:58:37,060
字幕
with the eyes slanted and all of that.

1008
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:40,490
字幕
There's nothing worse in a movie than when all of a sudden

1009
00:58:40,490 --> 00:58:42,450
字幕
some horrific stereotype shows up.

